Findings: Lung volumes remain low. Heart size is mildly enlarged but unchanged. The aortic knob is calcified. Diffuse parenchymal opacities with architectural distortion and bronchiectasis is re-demonstrate compatible with known chronic fibrotic lung disease, overall similar compared to the prior exam. Impression: Relatively similar appearance of diffuse chronic chronic lung disease. No new gross focal consolidation identified.
